  "text": "The tracheal mucosa of the cow is the source of tracheal antimicrobial peptide (TAP), a member of the b-defensin family of antibiotic peptides. TAP protects the upper airway of bovines from infection. The limited availability of bovine TAP (bTAP) prompted researchers to create transgenic mice expressing bTAP [CITATION_1] in their milk. They purified bTAP from milk by acid precipitation, reverse-phase HPLC, and ion-exchange chromatography. This milk-derived bTAP had antimicrobial activity against E. coli. The work may herald the expression of the bTAP in bovine milk and its evaluation or use as an antibiotic in agriculture and medicine.",
